  <prompt>
    Build the new `InsightsResponseRenderer` â€” the frontend component that consumes
    the `insights.query` chat-agent tool's response envelope (per Insights v1.0
    contract + v1.1 SSE/citations enhancements) and renders it correctly across
    FOUR distinct cases:

    1. **Playbook path** â€” `response.path === "playbook"` with
       `structuredResult.kind === "inference"`. Renders via the existing
       `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 017) in **static mode** for Insights
       v1.0 single-shot; in **streaming mode** when Wave F v1.1 SSE deltas arrive.
    2. **RAG path** â€” `response.path === "rag"` with citation-grounded prose
       (`answer` containing `[n]` citation tokens) + `citations[]` array. Renders
       `answer` text with clickable `[n]` tokens; the actual click handler is
       wired by task 027 (D2-17) â€” this task renders the tokens as interactive
       elements (Fluent v9 `Button` appearance="transparent" or equivalent) with
       a stub `onClick` that task 027 will replace.
    3. **Decline case** â€” `response.path === "playbook"` with
       `structuredResult.kind === "decline"` (200 OK, NOT error). Renders the
       envelope's `answer` (the `Explanation`) as plain text + `envelope.SuggestedActions`
       as a plain-text list. Per integration brief Â§11 quick-check 7. Fluent v9
       `MessageBar` intent="warning" framing.
    4. **Empty-result case** â€” `response.path === "rag"` AND `citations.length === 0`
       AND `answer === ""`. Renders a "couldn't find anything for that â€” try
       rephrasing or attaching files" hint per spec FR-13 acceptance / integration
       brief Â§4.4. MUST NOT render the empty `answer` verbatim (anti-hallucination
       contract).

    Per R5 CLAUDE.md Â§3.1 reuse mandate: the playbook path MUST consume the
    existing `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` from task 017 â€” do NOT build a parallel
    structured-output renderer. The widget already supports both streaming and
    static modes via `mode: 'streaming' | 'static'` + `INSIGHTS_PLAYBOOK_SCHEMA`
    (defined as a module-level export in task 017 per its reusability handshake).

    This task is pure frontend; no BFF code change. Publish-size delta = 0 MB.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React 19 + Fluent UI v9 frontend developer with experience building
    multi-path conditional renderers for chat-agent tool responses. Familiar with
    the Spaarke Insights v1.0 contract (response envelope, citation shape,
    decline shape), the `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` reusable contract (task
    017), the PaneEventBus dispatch pattern for citation-click routing (task 027
    consumes), and Fluent v9 semantic-token + dark-mode discipline (ADR-021).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `InsightsResponseRenderer.tsx` (plus per-case sub-renderers: `PlaybookResponseRenderer`,
    `RagResponseRenderer`, `DeclineResponseRenderer`, `EmptyResultHint`) is
    committed under
    `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/insights/`. The
    component: (1) discriminates over `response.path` + `structuredResult.kind`
    + empty-result heuristic; (2) routes playbook-path responses to
    `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` in static OR streaming mode (driven by whether
    Insights v1.1 SSE deltas are available â€” opt-in via `Accept: text/event-stream`
    per task 025); (3) renders RAG-path `answer` with clickable `[n]` citation
    tokens (click handler stubbed; task 027 wires the real dispatch); (4)
    renders decline case via `MessageBar` intent="warning" + plain-text
    `SuggestedActions`; (5) renders empty-result case with muted hint copy; (6)
    passes dark-mode visual check (Fluent v9 semantic tokens only); (7) passes
    the FULL-rigor quality gates (`code-review` + `adr-check`).

    Reusability acceptance: the playbook path renders via task 017's
    `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` with `mode: 'static'` + `INSIGHTS_PLAYBOOK_SCHEMA`
    + `prefilledFields` derived from `structuredResult.envelope` â€” ZERO widget
    code change required (UR-02 evidence from task 017's reusability handshake).
  </goal>

