    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Discriminated-union response envelope" location="N/A â€” new pattern; document inline">
        Type the Insights response envelope as a discriminated union over `path`
        and `structuredResult.kind`:
        ```typescript
        type InsightsResponse =
          | { path: 'playbook'; structuredResult: { kind: 'inference'; envelope: PlaybookEnvelope }; answer: string; citations: Citation[]; confidence: number; playbookId: string; diagnostics: Diagnostics }
          | { path: 'playbook'; structuredResult: { kind: 'decline'; envelope: DeclineResponse }; answer: string; citations: Citation[]; confidence: number; playbookId: string; diagnostics: Diagnostics }
          | { path: 'rag'; structuredResult: { kind: 'observation'; envelope: RagObservation }; answer: string; citations: Citation[]; confidence: number; playbookId: null; diagnostics: Diagnostics };
        ```
        The renderer discriminates via exhaustive `switch` on `path` then `kind`,
        producing TypeScript exhaustiveness guarantees. Empty-result is a
        sub-case detected on the RAG branch via runtime guard
        (`response.citations.length === 0 &amp;&amp; response.answer.trim() === ''`).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="StructuredOutputStreamWidget static-mode invocation" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx (task 017)">
        Per task 017's reusability handshake, the playbook-path renderer
        constructs `widgetData` as:
        ```typescript
        const widgetData = {
          mode: streamingEnabled ? 'streaming' : 'static',
          schema: INSIGHTS_PLAYBOOK_SCHEMA,
          prefilledFields: streamingEnabled ? undefined : envelopeToFields(envelope),
          correlationId: response.diagnostics.conversationId ?? generateCorrelationId(),
        };
        ```
        `streamingEnabled` is true iff Insights v1.1 SSE was opted-in by task
        025 AND the response was delivered as a stream. `envelopeToFields()` is
        a local helper that flattens `structuredResult.envelope` into the
        `prefilledFields` shape `INSIGHTS_PLAYBOOK_SCHEMA` expects (one key per
        schema field `path`).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Clickable `[n]` citation tokens (click stubbed)" location="N/A â€” new pattern; document inline">
        Render `response.answer` by tokenizing on `\[(\d+)\]` regex. Each
        capture becomes a Fluent v9 `Button` (appearance="transparent",
        size="small") with the visible label `[n]`; non-citation segments
        render as `Text`. The button's `onClick` is a STUB function this task
        leaves as `(citation) =&gt; console.debug('Citation clicked (task 027 wires)', citation)`.
        Task 027 (D2-17) replaces the stub with the real PaneEventBus
        `context.context_update` dispatch using `citation.observationId` /
        `citation.chunkId` to derive the source URL.

        Cite the seam in code comments:
        ```typescript
        // TODO(task-027): replace stub with PaneEventBus dispatch to open
        // citation source in FilePreviewContextWidget. See spec FR-14 + task
        // 027 (D2-17) for the v1.1 `citations[].href` plumbing.
        ```
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Decline + empty-result framing via Fluent v9" location="N/A â€” new pattern; document inline">
        Decline case: `MessageBar` with `intent="warning"` containing the
        `answer` text, followed by a list of `SuggestedActions` rendered as
        plain `Text` items (NOT Fluent `Button` â€” per integration brief Â§6 D3
        decision: plain strings in v1; actionable buttons â†’ R6 backlog).
        Empty-result case: muted `Text` (using `tokens.colorNeutralForeground3`)
        with hint copy "I couldn't find anything for that. Try rephrasing or
        attaching files." per spec FR-13. NO `MessageBar` â€” visually less
        alarming than a decline.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Semantic-token discipline (Fluent v9)" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx (task 017)">
        `makeStyles` + `tokens.*` references only. NO hex / rgba / `#fff`.
        Dark-mode parity is automatic when semantic tokens are used correctly.
        Typography via `tokens.fontSizeBase300` / `tokens.fontWeightSemibold`;
        spacing via `tokens.spacingHorizontal*` / `tokens.spacingVerticalM`;
        muted text via `tokens.colorNeutralForeground3`; brand accents via
        `tokens.colorBrandForeground1`.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 026 is the consumer-side bookend for R5's Insights tool integration.
      Task 024 registers the `insights.query` tool on `SprkChatAgent`; task 025
      handles subject resolution + HTTP transport; this task renders the
      response. The four cases â€” playbook / RAG / decline / empty-result â€”
      correspond to the four shapes the Insights v1.0 contract can return on
      200 OK (per integration brief Â§4). Error cases (12 codes per Â§5.1) are
      handled by task 029.

      The renderer lives in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/insights/`
      because it's the chat-pane response renderer â€” it sits between the
      Assistant's chat-message stream and the destination surfaces. For
      playbook responses, the destination IS the Workspace pane via the
      reusable `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 017); the renderer's job
      there is to MOUNT the widget with the right `widgetData`. For RAG
      responses, the destination is the chat-pane message bubble itself; the
      renderer produces inline prose with clickable citation tokens.

      The reusability claim of R5's platform-extension story (per SC-19) is
      most-visibly proven here: a different chat-tool tool (Insights) renders
      structured output via the SAME widget that streams Summarize output (per
      task 017). The reuse is configured via different `widgetData.schema` â€”
      not different widget code. If this task discovers the widget contract is
      insufficient, task 017 must extend additively (UR-02 escalation per
      CLAUDE.md Â§6).

      Task 027 (D2-17) wires the `[n]` citation click handler to PaneEventBus
      dispatch. Task 028 (D2-18) adds the confidence-floor badge. Both consume
      this renderer; both add additively. This task SHIPS with stub click
      handler + no confidence badge â€” the seam is clearly documented.
    </background>
