    <step order="3" name="Design Response-Shape Discrimination Types">
      Define the typed response envelope as a TypeScript discriminated union
      per the &lt;knowledge&gt; pattern. Place in a new module
      `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/insights/types.ts`:
      - `InsightsResponse` â€” discriminated union (playbook-inference /
        playbook-decline / rag-observation)
      - `PlaybookEnvelope` (typed shape of `InsightArtifact` from integration
        brief Â§4.1 â€” keep loose for v1.0; refine when Wave F lands)
      - `DeclineResponse` â€” `{ reason: string; minimumEvidenceNeeded?: string;
        suggestedActions: string[]; confidenceInDecline: number;
        explanation: string }`
      - `RagObservation` â€” `{ results: unknown[]; summary: string }`
      - `Citation` â€” `{ n: number; source: string; excerpt: string;
        observationId?: string; chunkId: string; href?: string | null }` (note:
        `href` is v1.1 optional per Wave F; v1.0 absent)
      - `Diagnostics` â€” `{ intentSource: 'classifier' | 'forceMode' |
        'classifier-fallback'; classifierBelowThreshold: boolean; elapsedMs:
        number; cacheHit: boolean; conversationId?: string }`

      Author a runtime guard `isEmptyResult(response: InsightsResponse): boolean`
      that returns true iff `response.path === 'rag' &amp;&amp; response.citations.length === 0 &amp;&amp; response.answer.trim() === ''`.

      Author a runtime guard `isDecline(response: InsightsResponse): boolean`
      that returns true iff `response.path === 'playbook' &amp;&amp; response.structuredResult.kind === 'decline'`.
